parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The excessive heat generated by the exhaust system can cause the plastic fender to melt, deform, or catch fire, leading to a potential fire hazard and risk of vehicle damage.
symptoms: The exhaust pipes
muffler
or heat shield become extremely hot
glowing red or orange
and can cause the surrounding plastic components to melt
deform
or catch fire. The heat can also cause the stick-on heat shield to lose its adhesiveness and fall off.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The poorly designed exhaust system can cause the exhaust components to overheat, leading to fires, burns, and damage to the vehicle and surrounding environment. This can result in serious injuries, fatalities, and property damage.
symptoms: The exhaust system glows red hot
the muffler reaches extremely high temperatures
the plastic fenders and surrounding areas become untouchable
the rear tire becomes extremely hot
and grass or other flammable materials near the exhaust can catch fire.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Electrical System Failure due to Water Ingress
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The electrical system failure can cause the battery to drain, leading to a loss of power and potentially leaving the driver stranded. Water ingress can also cause electrical shorts, which can lead to fires or other safety hazards.
symptoms: The electrical system shorts out when the vehicle gets wet
the battery drains
the drive belt slips due to water ingress.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The muffler overheating can cause a high risk of fire, especially when in contact with flammable materials such as brush. The excessive heat can also damage plastic body parts and potentially cause injuries.
symptoms: The muffler becomes red hot with normal use
the plastic in the area of the muffler and heat shield becomes too hot to touch
the plastic body parts may melt.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The excessive heat generated by the exhaust system can cause discomfort to the rider, melt plastic components, and pose a fire hazard to the vehicle and surrounding environment, including national forests.
symptoms: The muffler glows orange
plastic fenders melt
excessive heat emanating from the exhaust system
discomfort to the rider.
